cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with a policy learning approach for mapping visual inputs to driving controls, which involves leveraging side information on semantics and affordances of objects in the scene from a secondary teacher model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with visual inputs and semantic segmentation. Additionally, the use of a teacher-student model for policy learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on driving controls and traffic rules suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of intention values for driving controls suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the real-time aspect of the model suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
